053/**
054 * Simplex noise functions, in 2D, 3D, 4D, 5D, and 6D, with 4D and 6D as options for generating seamlessly-tiling noise
055 * using {@link Noise#seamless2D(double[][], long, int, Noise.Noise4D)} and/or
056 * {@link Noise#seamless3D(double[][][], long, int, Noise.Noise6D)}. All functions can take a long seed that should
057 * significantly change the pattern of noise produced. Incorporates code from Joise; the full library is available at
058 * https://github.com/SudoPlayGames/Joise , and this class adds rather significant optimization in a few methods,
059 * especially 6D noise. Joise is derived from the Accidental Noise Library, available in C++ at
060 * http://accidentalnoise.sourceforge.net/index.html . Both Joise and ANL have many features that SquidLib has not (yet)
061 * incorporated, but now that SquidLib has seamless noise, that's a nice feature that would have needed Joise before.
062 * This also supplies 5D noise, which doesn't have an immediate application like taking 6D noise and making 3D seamless
063 * noise, but still has plenty of uses. <a href="http://yellowstonegames.github.io/SquidLib/AnimatedChangingGlobe.gif">This
064 * world GIF</a> was made using 5D noise, for instance, using a cycle through the 4th and 5th dimensions to alter the
065 * globe in a way that loops. You'd probably find yourself mostly using 2D through 4D, though, with 4D useful for 3D
066 * shapes that change linearly over time.
067 */
068public class SeededNoise implements Noise.Noise2D, Noise.Noise3D, Noise.Noise4D, Noise.Noise5D, Noise.Noise6D {

081    /**
082     * Computes the hash for a 3D int point and its dot product with a 3D double point as one step.
083     * @param seed
084     * @param x
085     * @param y
086     * @param z
087     * @param xd
088     * @param yd
089     * @param zd
090     * @return a double between -1.2571 and 1.2571, exclusive
091     */
092    protected static double gradCoord3D(long seed, int x, int y, int z, double xd, double yd, double zd) {
093        final int hash = HastyPointHash.hash32(x, y, z, seed) * 3;
094        return xd * grad3d[hash] + yd * grad3d[hash + 1] + zd * grad3d[hash + 2];
095    }
096    protected static double gradCoord5D(long seed, int x, int y, int z, int w, int u, double xd, double yd, double zd, double wd, double ud) {
097        final int hash = HastyPointHash.hash256(x, y, z, w, u, seed) * 5;
098        return xd * grad5d[hash] + yd * grad5d[hash + 1] + zd * grad5d[hash + 2] + wd * grad5d[hash + 3] + ud * grad5d[hash + 4];
099    }

154    protected static final double F2 = 0.36602540378443864676372317075294,
155            G2 = 0.21132486540518711774542560974902,
156            F3 = 1.0 / 3.0,
157            G3 = 1.0 / 6.0,
158            F4 = (Math.sqrt(5.0) - 1.0) * 0.25,
159            G4 = (5.0 - Math.sqrt(5.0)) * 0.05,
160            LIMIT4 = 0.62,
161            F5 = (Math.sqrt(6.0) - 1.0) / 5.0,
162            G5 = (6.0 - Math.sqrt(6.0)) / 30.0,
163            LIMIT5 = 0.7,
164            F6 = (Math.sqrt(7.0) - 1.0) / 6.0,
165            G6 = F6 / (1.0 + 6.0 * F6),
166            LIMIT6 = 0.8375;

168    public static double noise(final double x, final double y, final long seed) {
169        final double s = (x + y) * F2;
170        final int i = fastFloor(x + s),
171                j = fastFloor(y + s);
172        final double t = (i + j) * G2,
173                X0 = i - t,
174                Y0 = j - t,
175                x0 = x - X0,
176                y0 = y - Y0;
177        int i1, j1;
178        if (x0 > y0) {
179            i1 = 1;
180            j1 = 0;
181        } else {
182            i1 = 0;
183            j1 = 1;
184        }
185        final double
186                x1 = x0 - i1 + G2,
187                y1 = y0 - j1 + G2,
188                x2 = x0 - 1 + 2 * G2,
189                y2 = y0 - 1 + 2 * G2;
190        double n = 0.0;
191        final int
192                gi0 = hash256(i, j, seed),
193                gi1 = hash256(i + i1, j + j1, seed),
194                gi2 = hash256(i + 1, j + 1, seed);
195        // Calculate the contribution from the three corners for 2D gradient
196        double t0 = 0.75 - x0 * x0 - y0 * y0;
197        if (t0 > 0) {
198            t0 *= t0;
199            n += t0 * t0 * (grad2d[gi0][0] * x0 + grad2d[gi0][1] * y0);
200        }
201        double t1 = 0.75 - x1 * x1 - y1 * y1;
202        if (t1 > 0) {
203            t1 *= t1;
204            n += t1 * t1 * (grad2d[gi1][0] * x1 + grad2d[gi1][1] * y1);
205        }
206        double t2 = 0.75 - x2 * x2 - y2 * y2;
207        if (t2 > 0)  {
208            t2 *= t2;
209            n += t2 * t2 * (grad2d[gi2][0] * x2 + grad2d[gi2][1] * y2);
210        }
211        // Add contributions from each corner to get the final noise value.
212        // The result is clamped to return values in the interval [-1,1].
213        return Math.max(-1.0, Math.min(1.0, 9.125f * n));

240    public static double noise(final double x, final double y, final double z, final long seed) {
241        double n = 0.0;
242        final double s = (x + y + z) * F3;
243        final int i = fastFloor(x + s),
244                j = fastFloor(y + s),
245                k = fastFloor(z + s);
246
247        final double t = (i + j + k) * G3;
248        final double X0 = i - t, Y0 = j - t, Z0 = k - t,
249                x0 = x - X0, y0 = y - Y0, z0 = z - Z0;
250
251        int i1, j1, k1;
252        int i2, j2, k2;
253
254        if (x0 >= y0) {
255            if (y0 >= z0) {
256                i1 = 1;
257                j1 = 0;
258                k1 = 0;
259                i2 = 1;
260                j2 = 1;
261                k2 = 0;
262            } else if (x0 >= z0) {
263                i1 = 1;
264                j1 = 0;
265                k1 = 0;
266                i2 = 1;
267                j2 = 0;
268                k2 = 1;
269            } else {
270                i1 = 0;
271                j1 = 0;
272                k1 = 1;
273                i2 = 1;
274                j2 = 0;
275                k2 = 1;
276            }
277        } else {
278            if (y0 < z0) {
279                i1 = 0;
280                j1 = 0;
281                k1 = 1;
282                i2 = 0;
283                j2 = 1;
284                k2 = 1;
285            } else if (x0 < z0) {
286                i1 = 0;
287                j1 = 1;
288                k1 = 0;
289                i2 = 0;
290                j2 = 1;
291                k2 = 1;
292            } else {
293                i1 = 0;
294                j1 = 1;
295                k1 = 0;
296                i2 = 1;
297                j2 = 1;
298                k2 = 0;
299            }
300        }
301
302        double x1 = x0 - i1 + G3; // Offsets for second corner in (x,y,z) coords
303        double y1 = y0 - j1 + G3;
304        double z1 = z0 - k1 + G3;
305        double x2 = x0 - i2 + F3; // Offsets for third corner in (x,y,z) coords
306        double y2 = y0 - j2 + F3;
307        double z2 = z0 - k2 + F3;
308        double x3 = x0 - 0.5; // Offsets for last corner in (x,y,z) coords
309        double y3 = y0 - 0.5;
310        double z3 = z0 - 0.5;
311
312        // Calculate the contribution from the four corners
313        double t0 = 0.6 - x0 * x0 - y0 * y0 - z0 * z0;
314        if (t0 > 0) {
315            t0 *= t0;
316            n += t0 * t0 * gradCoord3D(seed, i, j, k, x0, y0, z0);
317        }
318        double t1 = 0.6 - x1 * x1 - y1 * y1 - z1 * z1;
319        if (t1 > 0) {
320            t1 *= t1;
321            n += t1 * t1 * gradCoord3D(seed, i + i1, j + j1, k + k1, x1, y1, z1);
322        }
323        double t2 = 0.6 - x2 * x2 - y2 * y2 - z2 * z2;
324        if (t2 > 0) {
325            t2 *= t2;
326            n += t2 * t2 * gradCoord3D(seed, i + i2, j + j2, k + k2, x2, y2, z2);
327        }
328        double t3 = 0.6 - x3 * x3 - y3 * y3 - z3 * z3;
329        if (t3 > 0) {
330            t3 *= t3;
331            n += t3 * t3 * gradCoord3D(seed, i + 1, j + 1, k + 1, x3, y3, z3);
332        }
333        // Add contributions from each corner to get the final noise value.
334        // The result is clamped to stay just inside [-1,1]
335        return Math.max(-1.0, Math.min(1.0, 31.5 * n));
336        //return (32.0 * n) * 1.25086885 + 0.0003194984;
337    }

339    public static double noise(final double x, final double y, final double z, final double w, final long seed) {
340        double n = 0.0;
341        final double s = (x + y + z + w) * F4;
342        final int i = fastFloor(x + s), j = fastFloor(y + s), k = fastFloor(z + s), l = fastFloor(w + s);
343        final double[] gradient4DLUT = grad4d;
344        final double t = (i + j + k + l) * G4,
345                X0 = i - t,
346                Y0 = j - t,
347                Z0 = k - t,
348                W0 = l - t,
349                x0 = x - X0,
350                y0 = y - Y0,
351                z0 = z - Z0,
352                w0 = w - W0;
353        final int c = (x0 > y0 ? 128 : 0) | (x0 > z0 ? 64 : 0) | (y0 > z0 ? 32 : 0) | (x0 > w0 ? 16 : 0) | (y0 > w0 ? 8 : 0) | (z0 > w0 ? 4 : 0);
354        final int i1 = SIMPLEX_4D[c] >>> 2,
355                j1 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 1] >>> 2,
356                k1 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 2] >>> 2,
357                l1 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 3] >>> 2,
358                i2 = SIMPLEX_4D[c] >>> 1 & 1,
359                j2 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 1] >>> 1 & 1,
360                k2 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 2] >>> 1 & 1,
361                l2 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 3] >>> 1 & 1,
362                i3 = SIMPLEX_4D[c] & 1,
363                j3 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 1] & 1,
364                k3 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 2] & 1,
365                l3 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 3] & 1;
366        final double x1 = x0 - i1 + G4,
367                y1 = y0 - j1 + G4,
368                z1 = z0 - k1 + G4,
369                w1 = w0 - l1 + G4,
370                x2 = x0 - i2 + 2 * G4,
371                y2 = y0 - j2 + 2 * G4,
372                z2 = z0 - k2 + 2 * G4,
373                w2 = w0 - l2 + 2 * G4,
374                x3 = x0 - i3 + 3 * G4,
375                y3 = y0 - j3 + 3 * G4,
376                z3 = z0 - k3 + 3 * G4,
377                w3 = w0 - l3 + 3 * G4,
378                x4 = x0 - 1 + 4 * G4,
379                y4 = y0 - 1 + 4 * G4,
380                z4 = z0 - 1 + 4 * G4,
381                w4 = w0 - 1 + 4 * G4;
382        final int h0 = (hash256(i, j, k, l, seed) & 0xFC),
383                h1 = (hash256(i + i1, j + j1, k + k1, l + l1, seed) & 0xFC),
384                h2 = (hash256(i + i2, j + j2, k + k2, l + l2, seed) & 0xFC),
385                h3 = (hash256(i + i3, j + j3, k + k3, l + l3, seed) & 0xFC),
386                h4 = (hash256(i + 1, j + 1, k + 1, l + 1, seed) & 0xFC);
387        double t0 = LIMIT4 - x0 * x0 - y0 * y0 - z0 * z0 - w0 * w0;
388        if(t0 > 0) {
389            t0 *= t0;
390            n += t0 * t0 * (x0 * gradient4DLUT[h0] + y0 * gradient4DLUT[h0 | 1] + z0 * gradient4DLUT[h0 | 2] + w0 * gradient4DLUT[h0 | 3]);
391        }
392        double t1 = LIMIT4 - x1 * x1 - y1 * y1 - z1 * z1 - w1 * w1;
393        if (t1 > 0) {
394            t1 *= t1;
395            n += t1 * t1 * (x1 * gradient4DLUT[h1] + y1 * gradient4DLUT[h1 | 1] + z1 * gradient4DLUT[h1 | 2] + w1 * gradient4DLUT[h1 | 3]);
396        }
397        double t2 = LIMIT4 - x2 * x2 - y2 * y2 - z2 * z2 - w2 * w2;
398        if (t2 > 0) {
399            t2 *= t2;
400            n += t2 * t2 * (x2 * gradient4DLUT[h2] + y2 * gradient4DLUT[h2 | 1] + z2 * gradient4DLUT[h2 | 2] + w2 * gradient4DLUT[h2 | 3]);
401        }
402        double t3 = LIMIT4 - x3 * x3 - y3 * y3 - z3 * z3 - w3 * w3;
403        if (t3 > 0) {
404            t3 *= t3;
405            n += t3 * t3 * (x3 * gradient4DLUT[h3] + y3 * gradient4DLUT[h3 | 1] + z3 * gradient4DLUT[h3 | 2] + w3 * gradient4DLUT[h3 | 3]);
406        }
407        double t4 = LIMIT4 - x4 * x4 - y4 * y4 - z4 * z4 - w4 * w4;
408        if (t4 > 0) {
409            t4 *= t4;
410            n += t4 * t4 * (x4 * gradient4DLUT[h4] + y4 * gradient4DLUT[h4 | 1] + z4 * gradient4DLUT[h4 | 2] + w4 * gradient4DLUT[h4 | 3]);
411        }
412        //return NumberTools.bounce(5.0 + 41.0 * n);
413        return Math.max(-1.0, Math.min(1.0, 14.75 * n));
414    }

416    /**
417     * Thanks to Mark A. Ropper for
418     * <a href="https://computergraphics.stackexchange.com/questions/6408/what-might-be-causing-these-artifacts-in-5d-6d-simplex-noise">this implementation</a>.
419     * @param x x coordinate
420     * @param y y coordinate
421     * @param z z coordinate
422     * @param w w coordinate (4th dimension)
423     * @param u u coordinate (5th dimension)
424     * @param seed long value that should completely change the noise if it changes even slightly
425     * @return a continuous noise value between -1.0 and 1.0, both inclusive
426     */
427    public static double noise(final double x, final double y, final double z, final double w, final double u, final long seed) {
428        double n0, n1, n2, n3, n4, n5;
429        double t = (x + y + z + w + u) * F5;
430        int i = fastFloor(x + t);
431        int j = fastFloor(y + t);
432        int k = fastFloor(z + t);
433        int l = fastFloor(w + t);
434        int h = fastFloor(u + t);
435        t = (i + j + k + l + h) * G5;
436        double X0 = i - t;
437        double Y0 = j - t;
438        double Z0 = k - t;
439        double W0 = l - t;
440        double U0 = h - t;
441        double x0 = x - X0;
442        double y0 = y - Y0;
443        double z0 = z - Z0;
444        double w0 = w - W0;
445        double u0 = u - U0;
446
447        int rankx = 0;
448        int ranky = 0;
449        int rankz = 0;
450        int rankw = 0;
451        int ranku = 0;
452
453        if (x0 > y0) rankx++; else ranky++;
454        if (x0 > z0) rankx++; else rankz++;
455        if (x0 > w0) rankx++; else rankw++;
456        if (x0 > u0) rankx++; else ranku++;
457
458        if (y0 > z0) ranky++; else rankz++;
459        if (y0 > w0) ranky++; else rankw++;
460        if (y0 > u0) ranky++; else ranku++;
461
462        if (z0 > w0) rankz++; else rankw++;
463        if (z0 > u0) rankz++; else ranku++;
464
465        if (w0 > u0) rankw++; else ranku++;
466
467        int i1 = 3 - rankx >>> 31;
468        int j1 = 3 - ranky >>> 31;
469        int k1 = 3 - rankz >>> 31;
470        int l1 = 3 - rankw >>> 31;
471        int h1 = 3 - ranku >>> 31;
472
473        int i2 = 2 - rankx >>> 31;
474        int j2 = 2 - ranky >>> 31;
475        int k2 = 2 - rankz >>> 31;
476        int l2 = 2 - rankw >>> 31;
477        int h2 = 2 - ranku >>> 31;
478
479        int i3 = 1 - rankx >>> 31;
480        int j3 = 1 - ranky >>> 31;
481        int k3 = 1 - rankz >>> 31;
482        int l3 = 1 - rankw >>> 31;
483        int h3 = 1 - ranku >>> 31;
484

585    public static double noise(final double x, final double y, final double z,
586                               final double w, final double u, final double v, final long seed) {
587        final double s = (x + y + z + w + u + v) * F6;
588
589        final int skewX = fastFloor(x + s), skewY = fastFloor(y + s), skewZ = fastFloor(z + s),
590                skewW = fastFloor(w + s), skewU = fastFloor(u + s), skewV = fastFloor(v + s);
591        final double[] m = mShared, cellDist = cellDistShared, gradient6DLUT = SeededNoise.grad6d;
592        final int[] distOrder = distOrderShared,
593                intLoc = intLocShared;
594        intLoc[0] = skewX;
595        intLoc[1] = skewY;
596        intLoc[2] = skewZ;
597        intLoc[3] = skewW;
598        intLoc[4] = skewU;
599        intLoc[5] = skewV;
600
601        final double unskew = (skewX + skewY + skewZ + skewW + skewU + skewV) * G6;
602        cellDist[0] = x - skewX + unskew;
603        cellDist[1] = y - skewY + unskew;
604        cellDist[2] = z - skewZ + unskew;
605        cellDist[3] = w - skewW + unskew;
606        cellDist[4] = u - skewU + unskew;
607        cellDist[5] = v - skewV + unskew;

610        int o1 = (cellDist[1]<=cellDist[0]?1:0)+(cellDist[1]<cellDist[2]?1:0)+(cellDist[1]<cellDist[3]?1:0)+(cellDist[1]<cellDist[4]?1:0)+(cellDist[1]<cellDist[5]?1:0);
611        int o2 = (cellDist[2]<=cellDist[0]?1:0)+(cellDist[2]<=cellDist[1]?1:0)+(cellDist[2]<cellDist[3]?1:0)+(cellDist[2]<cellDist[4]?1:0)+(cellDist[2]<cellDist[5]?1:0);

627            if (c != -1) intLoc[distOrder[c]]++;

629            m[0] = cellDist[0] - (intLoc[0] - skewX) + skewOffset;
630            m[1] = cellDist[1] - (intLoc[1] - skewY) + skewOffset;

634            m[5] = cellDist[5] - (intLoc[5] - skewV) + skewOffset;

639                tc -= m[d] * m[d];
640            }

642            if (tc > 0) {
643                final int h = hash256(intLoc[0], intLoc[1], intLoc[2], intLoc[3],
644                        intLoc[4], intLoc[5], seed) * 6;

647                        + gradient6DLUT[h + 4] * m[4] + gradient6DLUT[h + 5] * m[5];
648                tc *= tc;
649                n += gr * tc * tc;
650            }
651            skewOffset += G6;
652        }
